1.title: Socorro
1.plot: Three hundred and seventy miles off the coast of Mexico in the eastern Pacific, the waters surrounding Socorro Island are home to some of the world's largest marine life. Take a deep dive through surging currents and majestic coral reefs with whale sharks, giant manta rays, and more.

2.title: Cocos Island
2.plot: Jacques cousteau once called cocos Island "the most beautiful island in the world." beyond its pristine rainforest is a marine wilderness brimming with multicolored fish, enormous sea turtles, and vast schools of sharks.

3.title: Roatan
3.plot: Forty miles north of Honduras, near the bay Island of roatan, is a spectacular and pristinely preserved coral atoll: the mesoamerican reef. explore the abundant and diverse marine life, lush vegetation, and magnificent caves of this rare underwater wonder.

4.title: Cozumel
4.plot: Explore the wild blue caribbean waters of cozumel, a lush paradise packed with marine surprises. from the spectacular paso del cedral coral reef to the world's longest subterranean underwater cave system, go where only the bravest divers dare venture.

5.title: Belize
5.plot: The Belize Barrier Reef is the second largest coral reef system in the world. Estimated to be nearly 4,000 years old, its waters are home to an immense marine ecosystem. Explore a deep blue wilderness brimming with rare, exotic fish, sea turtles, sharks, and huge green morays.

6.title: Bahamas
6.plot: Across the 3,000 scattered islands of the Bahamas lie visions of unexpected wonder. Experience its unique natural marvels--from towering pine forests to tangled mangrove swamps, to a mysterious labyrinth of underwater caves.

imdb.title: Great Blue Wild
plot: To catch a glimpse of some of the most spectacular natural wonders on the planet, you have to journey deep beneath the oceans. Dive into lush undersea gardens filled with vibrant vistas and otherworldly creatures.
